AddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Spec Points</span><hr size=1> I have to agree that the savage is getting the short end on the spec points.<br>
A beserker gets 2x and has three areas in which to spec... Axe, Left Axe, and Parry. I really have not seen a beserker spec anything other than those 3.<br>
The savage gets 1.5x and has three areas to spec in... Savagery, Hand-to-Hand, and Parry. He also is currently getting less HP than the beserker (but our good TL is trying to get that fixed).<br>
So my fellow savages, the simple fact of the matter is the savage will not be as good of a tank as the beserker.<br>
He does, however, have the advantage in a faster attack rate than the above beserker with some good tricks up his sleeve from the savagery skill list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kintrik@lighttanksofdaoc>Kintrik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#000000>(11/26/02 9:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spec Points</span><hr size=1> Trev,<br>
<br>
yes H2H is combinedweapon, dual wield.<br>
<br>
but we still need to train 3 lines.<br>
<br>
Zerker train 3 lines, 2 spec points. melee class.  light tank.<br>
<br>
skald train 3 lines, 1.5 points. support/melee class. chain armor<br>
<br>
warriors. train 3 lines, 2 spec points. heavy tank. chain<br>
<br>
thanes. train 4 lines, 2 points. melee/gimp caster class. chain<br>
<br>
savage, train 3 lines. 1.5 points. melee class, damage based on defense. super light tank(unless we get moved to the tank hp/damage table)<br>
<br>
now so you don't say we get 2 specline for 1 so 2 points insn't an option.<br>
<br>
champion. hybrid.  has large weapon spec.  one spec line for bot, alows use of 2h weapons, slash and crush. with large weapon ther is no need ot spec in slash or crush.  have 2 spec points.  other then LW. only need ot spec in 2 other lines. valor and parry.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#000000>(11/26/02 11:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Intro</span><hr size=1> My troll savage has 86 CON at level 50 (10 starter and 6 from Aug Con I). He has, completely nekkid, 1059 HP. With 211 CON, he has 1556hp. With 286 (I think) CON, he has 2126hp.<br>
<br>
I can't comment on HTH damage yet, because the recipes for level 51 HTH weapons aren't in yet. However, unlike the Berserker who has to spec Axe, Left Axe, and Parry, if we wanted the same we could just spec HTH and Parry. There's no need for us to spec weapon AND dual wield ability - they're both combined in HTH.<br>
<br>
But, I'm keeping an eye on how things are to see if we need more spec points.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/trevanti/savagebanner5.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Nightbird</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#000000>(12/2/02 12:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Stat increase per lvl?</span><hr size=1> From my understanding HTH damage is based off Dex/Str, if this is true why isn't str one of the stats that raises atleast every other lvl?  I've seen that it's Dex-Quick-Con, why quick over str when that's our damage modifier?  Or are Savages supposed to be dex monkeys that, while not doing the same amount of damage as any of the other light tank/dual wielders, they hit alot faster and get hit less? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#000000>(12/2/02 4:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Intro</span><hr size=1> With the recent Evade cap, I'm asking that the stats be changed to DEX/STR/CON...  right now the stats are DEX/QUI/STR, but QUI isn't nearly as important with us so close to the 50% cap with simply having 20% Evade IV and a 21% Evade buff at spec 39. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START-